8/10: Naresh> There is only one component in the sequence and iLO side it was observed that "BundleUpdateInstallSetMetaDownloadStatus" got struck did not move after that. Due to that, it failed finally with FWE-158. We will open a defect with the iLO team.

8/10: Open new defect and map

<Ambika> 
No new bug required, submitting COM form asking customer to verify their proxy or firewall setting. 

Here installset sequence contains only 1 component and estimated installation time is 16 minutes. With some extra time given job is attempting to monitor the simple update task for 32minutes. But in all the 32 minutes, iLO is unable to download the installset sequence and all the COM's retry got exhausted so JOB ended with FWE-158 error code, which is as expected. 

Looks this customer has some configuration issue (proxy/firewall)  due to which iLO is unable to download the installset sequence. Ideally connectivity test should capture this, but the test is taking 24minutes to complete and JOB currently doesn't wait for 24 minutes so the test results were not considered originally and the job was not able to fail with FWVE-104 error code. Some corner case, connectivity test takes more time is a known problem and we have made additional checks in COM code to handle that to some extent.

Exception occurred while executing FirmwareUpdate.New job: 41266ec0-6afe-40c0-9fec-2e9ebceeae13 for resource P53921-B21+CZ233606NL/compute-ops-mgmt/server. StateChangeReason: {'message_id': 'FWE-108'} Error:: JobException : BundleUpdateComponentDownloadFailed as ['cp069008.exe', 'InternalError']

Root cause discussed with iLO_PE dev team,
Error downloading component from default Url. err = -9,

The scsinet error code -9 shows that SCSI_ERR_OP_FAILED  (-9) Read or other network operation failed.

->This error code (-9) is typically returned when a read operation or network communication fails unexpectedly.

->It may indicate issues such as network timeouts, connection drops, data corruption, or server-side failures during SCSI operations.

->The network connection was closed or interrupted before the full data could be read.
 
Workaround:
Request you to retry again uploading the component, check network stability , verify remote server not closing the connection before the data tranfer. 

Sent comform to customer to check network connection during uploading of components and flashing of firmware
